content:
I’m locking this as Branch B: the active Professional system is the visual direction, and the HG Instagram link will be treated as channel context rather than a visual-source override because you selected structured placeholders. I’ll build the 11-slide deck now with concise executive speaker notes.`rg` isn’t available in this environment, so I’m switching to filesystem search with the same narrow target: the Simple Deck seed, layout library, and checklist.I’ve got the deck framework and layout library. The key constraint is to preserve the seed navigation and only author inside its slide slots, so the next step is rhythm and proof-object planning before the HTML write.Visual system: Professional tokens on a pale blue-white business canvas, Inter-based executive typography, blue as the primary structural accent, and industrial proof objects built from grids, tables, timelines, and labelled worksite placeholders. The deck rhythm will use light slides for explanation and dark slides for strategic emphasis, without decorative imagery.
Planned slide rhythm and proof objects:
1. `hero light center` Cover, title/subtitle only
2. `light` Why now, capability-to-trust gap diagram
3. `dark` Business understanding, contractor ecosystem grid
4. `light` Market focus, audience matrix
5. `hero dark center` Strategic positioning, core message billboard
6. `light` Four pillars, 2x2 framework
7. `dark` Monthly system, split bars plus channel cadence
8. `light` First 90 days, KPI table
9. `hero light center` 12-month roadmap, four-phase timeline
10. `dark` Partner role, execution operating model
11. `hero dark center` Success measures and 90-day recommendation.
I’m going to create `index.html` from the Simple Deck seed first, then patch only the token block, deck-specific CSS extensions, slide content, and notes. The navigation script will remain from the seed.The first full deck draft is in `index.html`: 11 slides, concise notes hidden in semantic speaker-note blocks, and only structured visual placeholders. I’m moving into validation now: placeholder sweep, theme rhythm, raw-color check, and script integrity.The structural checks are clean so far: 11 real slide sections, every slide has a label, no leftover replacement markers, no prohibited prepared-by/prepared-for/pricing copy, and the class rhythm alternates without three consecutive light or dark slides. Next I’m doing a render check because dense slides 8 and 10 are the likely overflow risks.
Playwright is not installed in the local runtime, so I can’t do a headless screenshot that way. I’m still validating the deck mechanically and will use the saved `index.html` preview as the handoff target.The HTML parser flagged one real issue: an ampersand inside slide 11’s `data-screen-label`. I’m escaping that now; the other parser messages are from the old validator not recognizing HTML5 sectioning tags.The critique pass found the main weakness: the accent was doing too much work in framework cards and charts. I’m tightening that now so each slide feels more executive and less visually noisy.One final cleanup: I’m removing internal seed comments from the deliverable source so the deck artifact stays client-facing while the proven navigation code remains intact.Built `index.html` as the canonical 11-slide deck and verified slide rhythm, labels, placeholders, copy constraints, and checklist basics; visual screenshot tooling was unavailable in this environment.

